{
  "stem": "18865.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 389.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We-- we lit the candles and sang.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We-- we knew all-- every one of the-- the Maoz Tzur from beginning to end.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I don't know how many stanzas there were.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And-- and we-- we lit the candles, and that was-- that was always nice, because outside of birthdays, so it was always good.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But the-- the-- the Seders when I was little were nice.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "My aunt, my grandmother's sister, led the Seder.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "My father didn't know anything about it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "He was not brought up in any shape or form in the Jew-- Jewish environment, but nothing-- not religious.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So my aunt used to do it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But then she moved to-- went to America, and I cannot remember any more Seders after that.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I think there was a public Seder once from-- from the Gemeinde, from the congregation, that the rabbi did, Dr.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Bluhm.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Did your mother light candles on Friday night?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, that we did.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "On Friday afternoons on a regular basis we took a bath, and then we prepared the couch in the [GERMAN], which was a-- like a living room.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we prepared it because Mutti would sit down with us, my sister and me, and she would tell us a story.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And she always started it by saying, do you want a happy one or a sad one?",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the answer was always a sad one.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And that's how we learned about operas, about classical-- about the classics, because she made that adjusting very wisely to our-- you know, between my sister and I, she kind of had to-- to graduate the age and so that we could understand it.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But we-- but they were almost always sad at the end, and that's what we liked.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, yes, I do, very well.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
